title.label: 5 Star game if they fix a few things

content.label:
I love this game. It's a good concept and the art is beautiful. It's definitely worth playing. 
However, there's some design and programming issues that hold it back. First, the campaign gets repetitive and grindy, so do the tower and boss modes. Those all could use some updates to keep them fresh. Currently, that makes pvp the mode where you'll spend most of your time. But, secondly, the matchmaking system for pvp is nonexistent. I've gone from three losses in a row to facing someone with almost 3 times as much power as I do. Which is ridiculous. It gets frustrating and losing stars that way makes pvp tough to keep playing. 

Other than that, I haven't hit any paywalls (yet), so I don't have any other complaints, but I do have a lot of recommendations.
10/10, would recommend.
